Parmesan Farrotto
  --America's Test Kitchen

3 c water
3 c chicken both
1/2 onion, finely chopped
1 1/2 c whole grain farro
4 tbsp butter, divided
1 clove garlic
2 tsp thyme, chopped
3/4 tsp black pepper
1 tsp salt
2  oz grated parmesan
2 tbsp parsley, chopped
2 tsp lemon juice

Heat water and broth over high heat, bring to a boil, reduce heat and cover. Pulse farro in blender 6 times, shooting for half the grains to be cracked. Heat 2 tbspbutter in dutch oven, once melted add onion and cook until it softens. Add garlic until fragrant, then add farro. Cook, stirring frequently, to toast until it smells nutty. Ladle in 5 c of broth, and bring to boil, cover, cook for 25 min, stirring occasionally. Farro should be al dente, most liquid absorbed. Add thyme, pepper, and salt; stir for 5 min constantly. Turn off heat, add parmesan, parsley, and lemon juice, 2 tbsp butter and stir until butter melts. Add rest of liquid to loosen it up. Taste and adjust seasoning as needed.
